1 12. The Town of Red Oak;
2 13. The Town of Bengal;
3 14. The Town of Talihina; and
4 15. The Talimena National Scenic Byway.
5 C. The Oklahoma Department of Transportation shall collaborate
6 with the Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation Department to maintain
7 online resources for the True Grit Trail, including but not limited
8 to:
9 1. A map of the True Grit Trail;
10 2. Information about each of the sites of significant interest
11 identified in this section; and
12 3. Historical context regarding the True Grit Trail.
13 D. The cost associated with signage required by this act may be
14 provided from private sources and may include the costs of the
15 initial erection of signs as well as the cost of potential
16 replacement or reconstruction of signs. Upon receiving adequate
17 funding, the Oklahoma Department of Transportation shall cause
18 suitable permanent markers to be placed as required by this act.
19 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
